    <stitle>DT/DTA-466 Diesel Engine Service (1990) - WATER PUMP AND THERMOSTAT - WATER PUMP - RECONDITIONING</stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="5">
        <title>RECONDITIONING</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title></title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">When servicing the water pump, always replace the water pump seal (3), O-Ring (16) if
                    applied, bearing assemblies (6), and front and rear bearing seals (5 and 11).
                </para>
                <figure id="ef4151013" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg10947" filename="../figcg1/CG10947.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 10.13. Cross Section of Current Water Pump.</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">1. Shaft</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">2. Impeller</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">3. Water Pump Seal</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">4. Bearing Housing</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">5. Rear Bearing Seal</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">6. Bearing Assembly</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">7. Inner Spacer</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">8. Outer Spacer</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">9. Retaining Ring Spacer</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">10. Retaining Ring</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">11. Bearing Front Seal</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">12. Wear Sleeve</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">13. Pulley Hub</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">14. Flange Lock Nut 3/4-16 Hex.</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">15. Spacer (Part of Item 6)</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">16. O-Ring</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef4151014" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg11728" filename="../figcg1/CG11728.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 10.14. Cross Section of Early Type Water Pump.</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">1. Shaft</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">2. Impeller</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">3. Water Pump Seal</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">4. Bearing Housing</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">5. Rear Bearing Seal</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">6. Bearing Assembly</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">7. Inner Spacer (if applied)</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">8. Outer Spacer</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">9. Retaining Ring Spacer</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">10. Retaining Ring</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">11. Bearing Front Seal</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">12. Wear Sleeve</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">13. Pulley Hub</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">14. Flange Lock Nut 3/4-16 Hex</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">15. Spacer (Part of Item 6)</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">16. O-Ring (if groove is provided)</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">17. Bearing Housing Dowel Pin (2)</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">18. Inspection Port</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">19. Water Pump Seal Seat</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Reassembly</title>
            <para>Reassemble the water pump as follows: (Reference numbers refer to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4151013">10.13</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                or
                <emph type="bold">
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4151014">10.14</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .)
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>A HIGH TEMPERATURE GREASE MUST BE USED DURING REASSEMBLY. THE GREASE SPECIFICATION (EMS
                        B27-5004 TYPE 1) IS MET BY AMOCO'S RYKON PREMIUM GREASE NO. 2 COLOR RED AND MAY BE OBTAINED
                        LOCALLY. IF A LOCAL DISTRIBUTOR CANNOT BE FOUND, CONTACT:
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">AMOCO OlL COMPANY</emph>
            </para>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">200 E. RANDOLPH DRIVE</emph>
            </para>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">CHICAGO, IL 60601</emph>
            </para>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">TELEPHONE: (312) 856-5111</emph>
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Apply a coat of Aviation Permatex&#8482; No. 3 to the rear bearing seal (5). See Detail
                    "C",
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4151013">10.13</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    or
                    <emph type="bold">
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4151014">10.14</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Pack the new rear seal (5) cavity full of grease (see
                    <emph type="bold">Note</emph>). Lubricate the rear seal O.D. and seal lip with grease.* Press the
                    new rear seal into the housing (4).
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Use Amoco Rykon Premium Grease No. 2 Color Red.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Prepack the rear roller bearing inner race assembly with grease.* Support the shaft (1)
                    at the impeller end and press the inner race assembly to bottom on the shoulder of the shaft.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lightly lubricate the seal surface on the shaft (1) and the O.D. of the shaft
                    installation sleeve with grease.* Install the shaft into the front of the pump with the installation
                    sleeve. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4151015">10.15</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the shaft installation sleeve.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Grease* the rear roller bearing (6) outer race and press into the housing (4) against
                    the shoulder.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the outer spacer (8).</para>
                <figure id="ef4151015" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg11637" filename="../figcg1/CG11637.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 10.15. Shaft Installation Sleeve and Old vs. New Style Water Pump Shaft.</caption>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>THE SHAFT INSTALLATION SLEEVE (FIGURE
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef4151015">10.15</hotlnk>) MUST BE USED TO INSTALL THE NEW STYLE SHAFT.
                            INSTALLING THE WATER PUMP SHAFT WITHOUT THE INSTALLATION SLEEVE COULD CAUSE REAR SEAL DAMAGE
                            AND/OR DISPLACEMENT. THE SHAFT INSTALLATION SLEEVE CAN BE MADE LOCALLY.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Press in outer race of the front bearing and make sure that outer bearing races and
                    spacers are bottomed.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the spacers (7 and 15).</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Fill in the cavity between the spacers with 0.5 oz. (16 cc) of grease (see
                    <emph type="bold">Note</emph>).
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Use Amoco Rykon Premium Grease No. 2 Color Red.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Prepack front roller bearing inner race assembly with grease (see
                    <emph type="bold">Note</emph>). Support shaft at impeller end and press inner race assembly until it
                    bottoms on shaft.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Use Amoco Rykon Premium Grease No. 2 Color Red.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the retaining ring spacer (9) and the retaining ring (10).</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Pack the spring area of the front seal (11) full of grease and lubricate the seal lip
                    with grease (see
                    <emph type="bold">Note</emph>).
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Use Amoco Rykon Premium Grease No. 2 Color Red.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the front seal (11) and the housing (4) against the retaining ring (10).</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lightly lubricate the seal surface of the wear sleeve ( 12).</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the wear sleeve (12).</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the pulley hub (13) onto the shaft (1).</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Apply clean engine oil to the threads and install the flange lock nut (14). Tighten the
                    shaft to the
                    <hotlnk document="e415_HL4151002.xml" xrefid="hl4151002">"SPECIAL TORQUES"</hotlnk>
                    by turning the internal hex at the end of the shaft, while holding the nut.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install a new O-Ring (16) (if applied) on the water pump seal (3) and press into the
                    bearing housing (4), using the water pump seal installation tool. (See Detail "B",
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4151013">10.13</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    or
                    <emph type="bold">
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4151014">10.14</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>AN O-RING IS NECESSARY ON COOLANT SEAL USED WITH NEW STYLE BEARING HOUSING WHICH HAS A
                            GROOVE PROVIDED (FIGURE
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef4151016">10.16</hotlnk>). WITH OLD STYLE BEARING HOUSING WHICH HAS NO
                            GROOVE AN O-RING MUST NOT BE USED ON THE COOLANT SEAL. INSTEAD APPLY PERMATEX #3 TO SEAL
                            O.D. BEFORE INSTALLING (FIGURE 10.17).
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">For those water pumps with a two-piece seal, install the coolant seal seat into the
                    impeller by moistening seal seat (19) and cup O.D. with water before assembly. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4151014">10.14</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    by hand, press the seal seat to bottom of impeller counter bore.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">For those water pumps with a one-piece seal apply two small drops of Loctite&#174; 290
                    to the shaft/coolant seal joint. Space each drop 180&#176; apart.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Support the shaft at the front end and push the housing down by hand.</para>
                <figure id="ef4151016" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg11730" filename="../figcg1/CG11730.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 10.16. Current Style Bearing Housing with Groove and Coolant Seal with O-Ring.
                    </caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">1. Groove</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">2. O-Ring</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">3. Coolant Seal</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">4. Bearing Housing</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef4151017" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg11729" filename="../figcg1/CG11729.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 10.17. Old Style Bearing Housing and Coolant Seal.</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">1. Coolant Seal</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">2. Bearing Housing</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Press the impeller onto the shaft supported on the front end as shown in
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk document="e415_226.xml" xrefid="ef4151018">10.18</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Prior to full installation of the impeller, place two 0.71 mm (0.028 in.) feeler gauges
                            under the impeller.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Verify impeller to housing clearance as follows:</para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>USE A SLEEVE (FIGURE
                            <hotlnk document="e415_226.xml" xrefid="ef4151018">10.18</hotlnk>) UNDER THE PRESS RAM WHEN
                            PRESSING ON THE IMPELLER BECAUSE THE SHAFT WILL PROTRUDE SLIGHTLY ABOVE
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">With the feeler gauge in place, press the impeller until the feeler gauges are snug.
                        Refer to
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk document="e415_226.xml" xrefid="ef4151018">10.18</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        .
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Refer to the
                        <hotlnk document="e415_HL4151001.xml" xrefid="hl4151001">"SPECIFICATIONS"</hotlnk>
                        for impeller to housing clearance.
                    </para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
